    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nRunning :norm commands on long visual selections takes forever especially if the command is nontrivial. Unlike macros, however, the work could be divided between several threads. This could be used for running a macro on every line for example though there are probably more advanced uses I am unaware of.\n\nI know this might be a very large task and is specific to a minority of use cases so I would be willing to try and implement it I am just wondering if there are any problems with the idea.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIf the selection that :norm is being applied to is larger than .e.g. 50000 lines, divide the lines into batches and run them on different threads",
